Florida law gives wide latitude to people claiming self-defense, and the jury was required to listen to the facts and decide whether the prosecution had proven, without a reasonable doubt, that Zimmerman did not feel in danger. That's a hard standard to reach, so as distressing as the not guilty verdict is to many people, it's an understandable conclusion.
